# Election Assistant — Environment Configuration
# Copy to .env.local and fill in your values. Never commit .env.local.

# ── Offline scripts only (not needed for the app to run) ─────────────────────
# Used by scripts/auto-score.ts to call Claude Sonnet for party score derivation.
# Get yours at: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ── Required ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google Gemini API key — required for AI follow-up questions, scoring, and results analysis
# Free key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...

# Mixpanel behavioral analytics — client-side token (safe to expose publicly)
# Get from: Mixpanel → Project Settings → Project Token
# Tip: create a separate dev project and use its token in .env.local
NEXT_PUBLIC_MIXPANEL_TOKEN=your_token_here

# ── Optional: LLM observability (Langfuse) ────────────────────────────────────
# Logs each conversation turn (session, model, input, output, errors) to Langfuse.
# Leave unset to bypass — Gemini is called directly with no conversation tracking.
# Sign up free: https://cloud.langfuse.com → create project → Settings → API Keys
LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=sk-lf-...
LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk-lf-...
# Optional: defaults to EU cloud. US region: https://us.cloud.langfuse.com
# LANGFUSE_BASE_URL=https://us.cloud.langfuse.com

# ── Optional: Quota monitoring (production only — Vercel cron) ─────────────────
# /api/quota-check runs hourly and posts to Slack when daily quota thresholds are
# crossed for the first time in a rolling hour window. Not needed locally unless
# you're testing the endpoint directly.

# Daily token limit for the active Gemini model. Update when you change models/tiers.
# Free tier (gemini-*-flash-lite): 250 000 tokens/day. See GCP quota page for paid tier.
# QUOTA_DAILY_TOKEN_LIMIT=250000

# Daily request limit. Free tier: 1 500 req/day.
# QUOTA_DAILY_REQUEST_LIMIT=1500

# Comma-separated % thresholds that trigger a Slack alert (first crossing per hour only).
# QUOTA_ALERT_THRESHOLDS=50,80,90

# Slack incoming webhook URL.
# Create: https://api.slack.com/apps → New app → Incoming Webhooks → Add Webhook → copy URL.
# QUOTA_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/...

# Random secret that protects /api/quota-check from public calls.
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32   (or `! openssl rand -hex 32` in Claude)
# Set the same value in Vercel dashboard. Omit entirely to allow unauthenticated access.
# QUOTA_CRON_SECRET=

# ── Optional: User feedback (Slack) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Incoming webhook URL for the #election-feedback Slack channel.
# Feedback submitted via the in-app widget on the results page is posted here.
# Create at: Slack → Your App → Incoming Webhooks → Add New Webhook to Workspace
# FEEDBACK_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/XXX/YYY/ZZZ

# ── Optional: Per-IP rate limiting (Upstash Redis — production only) ──────────
# Limits quiz entry (/prototype-e) to 10 sessions/IP/24h to prevent abuse.
# Without these vars the middleware is a no-op — no rate limiting in local dev.
# Setup: Vercel dashboard → Storage → Connect store → Upstash Redis (or KV)
# Vercel auto-injects KV_REST_API_URL and KV_REST_API_TOKEN — no manual copy needed in production.
# For local testing only, copy them from Vercel dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables.
# KV_REST_API_URL=https://...-...-...-....upstash.io
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=Axxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
